♪ For something more. ♪

12:11.630 --> 12:14.600
♪ Restless in the night. ♪

12:14.600 --> 12:17.770
♪ Burning like a light. ♪

12:17.770 --> 12:20.172
♪ Desperate in the night. ♪

12:20.172 --> 12:24.677
♪ For something more. ♪

12:24.677 --> 12:27.446
♪ Restless in the night. ♪

12:27.446 --> 12:30.483
♪ Burning like a light. ♪

12:30.483 --> 12:32.985
♪ Desperate in the night. ♪

12:32.985 --> 12:35.121
♪ For something more. ♪

12:35.121 --> 12:35.955
Yikes!

12:37.490 --> 12:38.324
Help!

12:40.726 --> 12:42.661
Bentley! We're saved!

12:44.330 --> 12:47.166
Aww Bentley, my hero!

12:47.166 --> 12:48.734
You've come to take me home.

12:49.902 --> 12:52.705
Oh, oh, oh, thank
you. Thank you.

12:55.074 --> 12:55.875
Help!

13:00.212 --> 13:01.847
I'm interrupting this program

13:01.847 --> 13:04.250
to bring you a public
service announcement.

13:04.250 --> 13:06.018
Have you seen these hoodlums?

13:06.018 --> 13:09.622
These hard-bitten miscreants
are wanted for dog napping.

13:09.622 --> 13:11.657
Any information as
to their whereabouts

13:11.657 --> 13:14.093
should be forwarded
to Sneer Central.

13:14.093 --> 13:16.529
He's taken his backpack,
sweater and flashlight,

13:16.529 --> 13:18.097
and his tape recorder.

13:18.097 --> 13:20.766
Only told us was he
didn't wanna go fishing.

13:20.766 --> 13:22.268
It's all my fault.

13:22.268 --> 13:23.803
I should have given
him the money.

13:23.803 --> 13:24.737
Come on.

13:24.737 --> 13:26.071
We gotta think logically.

13:26.071 --> 13:28.874
Now, where would Bentley
go needing a flashlight

13:28.874 --> 13:30.576
in broad daylight?

13:30.576 --> 13:32.578
Some place dark?

13:32.578 --> 13:35.748
With no electricity.
The Caverns?

13:35.748 --> 13:37.249
He knows better.

13:37.249 --> 13:40.252
Besides why on earth would
he go there by himself?

13:40.252 --> 13:42.154
For treasure!

13:42.154 --> 13:43.389
Listen to this.

13:43.389 --> 13:46.392
"Congratulations on
your wise decision

13:46.392 --> 13:49.195
to purchase one of
Colonel Jethro Smith's

13:49.195 --> 13:51.764
authentic personalized
treasure maps."

13:51.764 --> 13:53.032
It's a scam.

13:53.032 --> 13:56.101
The pigs sent away for
one in Mudman Comics.

13:56.101 --> 13:59.071
Pop confiscated it
and spent three days

13:59.071 --> 14:02.174
wandering around the
endless Echo Caverns.

14:02.174 --> 14:03.976
Oh Bentley.

14:03.976 --> 14:05.244
According to the map,

14:05.244 --> 14:07.446
that tunnel should
lead us out of here.

14:07.446 --> 14:09.014
It's worth a try.

14:12.651 --> 14:14.553
Oh! Another dead end!

14:15.888 --> 14:19.425
Oh, I wish you
wouldn't use that word.

14:19.425 --> 14:20.926
This doesn't make sense.

14:20.926 --> 14:22.361
Colonel Jethro's map says-

14:22.361 --> 14:25.764
Oh no!
Not Colonel Jethro!

14:25.764 --> 14:28.267
Why? What's wrong with Col-

14:31.403 --> 14:32.805
It's Snag!

14:32.805 --> 14:35.608
Oh, he's still out to get us!

14:35.608 --> 14:37.843
Get up here, Bentley!

14:37.843 --> 14:38.844
Ahh!

14:51.891 --> 14:53.692
I know it's
in here somewhere.

14:53.692 --> 14:55.661
The map's over 50 years old,

14:55.661 --> 14:57.162
but it's still the
most detailed map

14:57.162 --> 14:58.764
of the caverns ever made.

14:59.598 --> 15:00.532
Here it is.

15:00.532 --> 15:02.101
Well what are we wearing for?

15:02.101 --> 15:03.969
Let's hit the caverns!

15:06.605 --> 15:07.439
Oh dear.

15:07.439 --> 15:09.241
Sorry Professor!

15:09.241 --> 15:11.377
Where are you going
with that document?

15:11.377 --> 15:12.945
Sorry, no time to explain!

15:12.945 --> 15:15.514
You come back here right now,

15:15.514 --> 15:18.183
Or you're in a packet
of trouble, young lady!

15:18.183 --> 15:19.451
I say a packet!

15:22.154 --> 15:24.123
I'm coming.

15:25.157 --> 15:26.625
Please.

15:26.625 --> 15:29.795
Snag! My little Snagaroni!

15:29.795 --> 15:31.363
Good boy!

15:31.363 --> 15:34.099
What did those rotten
reprobates do to you?

15:34.099 --> 15:35.434
Oh, who cares?

15:35.434 --> 15:39.305
My blue ribbon, blue
point, oh my Snagaroons!

15:39.305 --> 15:41.640
We'll still win first prize.

15:41.640 --> 15:45.377
Hey, sit! Maladjusted mutt!

15:45.377 --> 15:48.047
Come back here you
cantankerous canine!

15:50.015 --> 15:51.684
Don't you wanna be a champion?

15:55.321 --> 15:56.689
Think of the prestige!

15:56.689 --> 15:58.057
Think of the money!

15:58.057 --> 16:00.192
Bentley!

16:00.192 --> 16:01.627
Answer us!

16:01.627 --> 16:03.095
Where are you?

16:03.095 --> 16:04.697
What if he's not
even down here?

16:04.697 --> 16:05.931
What if he is?

16:05.931 --> 16:08.767
We'll find him,
Lisa. I promise.

16:08.767 --> 16:11.236
Let's have another
look at that map.

16:11.236 --> 16:15.107
Get back here,
you flea-bitten flig!

16:15.107 --> 16:16.175
Snag?

16:16.175 --> 16:18.143
Get back here!

16:18.143 --> 16:19.211
Pop?

16:19.211 --> 16:20.312
Pop! Hey Pop!

16:22.147 --> 16:23.649
Good boy.

16:23.649 --> 16:24.883
Stay.

16:24.883 --> 16:26.151
Sit.

16:26.151 --> 16:27.019
Now. Lie down.

16:27.019 --> 16:28.554
Pop!

16:28.554 --> 16:29.421
Oh, hello son.

16:30.723 --> 16:33.292
What in the name of
spelunking are you doing here

16:33.292 --> 16:34.793
at this hour?

16:34.793 --> 16:37.463
Those overfed oinkers aren't
down here with you, are they?

16:37.463 --> 16:38.964
It's Bentley Mr Sneer.

16:38.964 --> 16:40.699
We think he's down
here somewhere.

16:40.699 --> 16:41.533
Lost.

16:41.533 --> 16:42.568
What is it, boy?

16:42.568 --> 16:43.469
Is it Bentley?

16:43.469 --> 16:44.770
Bentley!

16:44.770 --> 16:45.971
Bentley, answer me!

16:45.971 --> 16:48.107
Lisa! Come on,
we gotta stay calm.

16:48.107 --> 16:49.942
We've gotta think!

16:49.942 --> 16:51.710
Darn stupid kid.

16:51.710 --> 16:54.046
It'll take us days
to get to him.

16:54.046 --> 16:57.082
We don't have days.
We've got hours.

16:57.082 --> 16:58.317
What do you mean?

16:58.317 --> 17:00.652
Bentley's in
there, we're out here.

17:00.652 --> 17:02.021
This is the only way in,

17:02.021 --> 17:05.691
and this marks the
path of a stream.

17:05.691 --> 17:08.460
It must connect up with
Evergreen Lake somewhere.

17:08.460 --> 17:11.130
If there used to be a
stream flowing through here,

17:11.130 --> 17:13.432
where's all the water gone?

17:15.734 --> 17:17.069
We're sunk!

17:18.237 --> 17:20.806
We're nothing but shark food!

17:22.574 --> 17:25.677
Oh dear!

17:25.677 --> 17:26.512
Oh mom!

17:27.946 --> 17:30.315
Things haven't
worked out quite as planned.

17:30.315 --> 17:32.384
This might be the last
entry for a while.

17:33.352 --> 17:35.354
The air is getting bad.

17:35.354 --> 17:36.922
I must conserve oxygen.

17:38.657 --> 17:40.092
You don't even know

17:40.092 --> 17:42.528
if there is an underwater
entrance down here.

17:42.528 --> 17:44.063
There's gotta be!

17:44.063 --> 17:47.399
That underground stream
comes from somewhere, Pop!

17:47.399 --> 17:51.270
The map, says the caverns
go right out under the lake.

17:51.270 --> 17:52.738
All right.

17:52.738 --> 17:56.575
Just, just be careful Cedric
and bring Bentley back,

17:56.575 --> 17:59.511
because I wanna have a
serious chat with that boy.

18:22.201 --> 18:26.839
I was just thinking, if
we all drank a lot of water,

18:27.706 --> 18:29.341
maybe the level would drop.

18:30.542 --> 18:34.746
That's the dumbest
idea I've ever heard!

18:36.048 --> 18:37.883
Log of Bentley Expedition.

18:39.218 --> 18:41.453
Pressure is finally
beginning to take its toll.

18:43.355 --> 18:44.189
Hey! Look!

18:46.058 --> 18:47.826
Excuse me.

18:49.128 --> 18:50.863
Yes! We're saved!

18:50.863 --> 18:52.498
Bentley, you little idiot!

18:52.498 --> 18:54.133
Just wait till I
tell mom and dad!

18:54.133 --> 18:58.604
Well, I, boy, am
I glad to see you!

18:58.604 --> 19:01.773
You're looking pretty
good yourself, sis.

19:01.773 --> 19:03.809
What are
you three doing here?

19:03.809 --> 19:06.578
Drowning! Get us outta here!

19:06.578 --> 19:07.746
All right, everybody!

19:07.746 --> 19:09.148
let's share our tanks!

19:09.148 --> 19:10.315
Buddy system!

19:10.315 --> 19:11.984
Lisa, you take Bentley.

19:11.984 --> 19:13.218
I'll take two of the boys

19:13.218 --> 19:15.087
and you get the other one, Bert.

19:15.087 --> 19:16.622
Just breathe easy, Bentley.

19:28.734 --> 19:30.969
Bentley, my boy!
Cedric, are you all right?

19:30.969 --> 19:32.404
Piece of cake, Pop.

19:32.404 --> 19:33.572
Just fine.

19:33.572 --> 19:34.873
Thank you Mr. Sneer.

19:34.873 --> 19:36.942
Ha ha! Great.

19:36.942 --> 19:39.411
Uh, we're fine too, boss.

19:39.411 --> 19:41.747
What in the
name of water buffaloes

19:41.747 --> 19:43.081
are you doing here?

19:43.081 --> 19:43.916
Well, well, uh-

19:45.017 --> 19:46.251
Skip it!

19:46.251 --> 19:48.654
I'll deal with you water
logged warthogs later.

19:48.654 --> 19:49.922
Get in the boat.

19:51.490 --> 19:53.458
Well, I'll just
follow behind the boat,

19:53.458 --> 19:54.726
if you don't mind. Ha ha.

19:56.695 --> 19:59.364
Honestly, Bentley, I
don't know anyone else

19:59.364 --> 20:00.933
with a brother like you.

20:00.933 --> 20:03.168
The things I have
to put up with.

20:03.168 --> 20:04.803
Yeah, I know.

20:04.803 --> 20:07.005
Good thing I've got
a sister like you.

20:08.373 --> 20:10.175
Sometimes we all look

20:10.175 --> 20:12.411
for the easy way
out of our problems.

20:12.411 --> 20:15.881
But as Bentley found
out, making easy money is

20:15.881 --> 20:19.117
usually a lot more
difficult than it looks.

20:19.117 --> 20:21.587
I always knew you
were the best puppy, Broo!

20:21.587 --> 20:25.290
And now you've got
the award to prove it.

20:25.290 --> 20:27.092
Sit, Snag! Heel, boy!

20:30.095 --> 20:31.563
Darn mutt!

20:31.563 --> 20:34.066
I've got 15 minutes to
turn him into a show dog.

20:34.066 --> 20:35.100
He's up next!

20:36.835 --> 20:39.171
I wouldn't get
your hopes up, Pop.

20:39.171 --> 20:42.174
Hi, Mr Sneer. Thanks
for getting me this job.

20:42.174 --> 20:45.043
It's sure a lot easier than
getting money the easy way.

20:45.043 --> 20:47.279
Always. When this wraps up,

20:47.279 --> 20:49.681
there are a few things you
could do around the mansion,

20:49.681 --> 20:50.716
If you're up for it.

20:50.716 --> 20:52.317
You bet, Mr. Sneer.

20:52.317 --> 20:55.354
At this rate you'll get
a new car in no time, Bert.

20:55.354 --> 20:57.189
Not to mention the window.

20:57.189 --> 21:01.159
Oh, Mr Sneer, we're
almost ready for your dog.

21:01.159 --> 21:04.029
A blue something or other?

21:05.797 --> 21:08.000
He's just about ready.

21:08.000 --> 21:11.536
So young lady, I'll expect
you for work as usual,

21:11.536 --> 21:12.504
this afternoon?

21:12.504 --> 21:13.772
Yes, sir.

21:13.772 --> 21:15.974
And I'm sorry about the map.

21:15.974 --> 21:19.278
Oh, no harm done, my dear.

21:19.278 --> 21:21.913
I have a little
brother too, you know?

21:21.913 --> 21:24.349
Yeah. Funny things, brothers.

21:26.852 --> 21:30.355
Oh, that it! Hold him
Mr Sneer, hold him!

21:30.355 --> 21:33.425
Bring your dog to the ring!

21:35.994 --> 21:38.930
Last call for Cyril
Sneer and Snag!

21:39.765 --> 21:40.599
Last call!

21:58.917 --> 22:01.853
♪ When darkness falls. ♪

22:01.853 --> 22:05.691
♪ Leaving shadows
in the night. ♪

22:05.691 --> 22:08.327
♪ Don't be afraid. ♪

22:08.327 --> 22:12.731
♪ Wipe that fear
from your eyes. ♪

22:12.731 --> 22:15.667
♪ But desperate love. ♪

22:15.667 --> 22:19.471
♪ Keeps on driving you wrong. ♪

22:19.471 --> 22:22.574
♪ Don't be afraid. ♪

22:22.574 --> 22:26.311
♪ You're not alone. ♪

22:26.311 --> 22:29.514
♪ You can run with us. ♪

22:29.514 --> 22:33.552
♪ We got everything you need. ♪

22:33.552 --> 22:36.488
♪ Run with us. ♪

22:36.488 --> 22:40.826
♪ We are free. ♪

22:40.826 --> 22:43.495
♪ Come with us. ♪

22:43.495 --> 22:47.532
♪ I see passion in your eyes. ♪

22:47.532 --> 22:50.135
♪ Run with us. ♪
